Procedure $\operatorname{CutCake}(P, D, D_{P})$

- Find all the maximal intervals of minimum density $\rho_{\mathrm{min}}$ in the cake-cutting problem with cake $D$, players $P$, and solid valuation intervals $\mathcal{D}_{P}$. 
- Let $H_{1}=\left[h_{1}^{\prime},h_{1}^{\prime\prime}\right)$, $H_{2}=\left[h_{2}^{\prime},h_{2}^{\prime\prime}\right)$, ..., $H_{L}=\left[h_{L}^{\prime},h_{L}^{\prime\prime}\right)$ be all the maximal intervals of minimum density $\rho_{\mathrm{min}}$. $H_{1}, H_{2}, ..., H_{L}$ are mutually disjoint by Corollary 5. 
- For $\ell=1$ to $L$ do, 
  - cut cake $D$ at both endpoints $h_{\ell}^{\prime}, h_{\ell}^{\prime\prime}$ of $H_{\ell}$;
  - $R_{\ell}=\left\{k\in P \mid D_{k}\subseteq H_{\ell}, D_{k}\in\mathcal{D}_{P}\right\};\;\mathcal{D}_{R_{\ell}}=\left(D_{k}\in\mathcal{D}_{P}: k\in R_{\ell}\right)$;
  - $\operatorname{CutMaxInterval}(R_{\ell}, H_{\ell}, D_{R_{\ell}})$. 
- $P^{\prime}=P; D^{\prime}=D$; for $\ell=1$ to $L$ do, $P^{\prime}=P^{\prime}\setminus R_{\ell}; D^{\prime}=D^{\prime}\setminus H_{\ell}$. 
- If $P^{\prime}\neq\emptyset$ then // $P^{\prime}=P\setminus\sum_{\ell=1}^{L}R_{\ell}$ and $D^{\prime}=D\setminus\sum_{\ell=1}^{L}H_{\ell}$. 
  - $\mathcal{D}_{P^{\prime}}^{\prime}=\emptyset$;
  - For each $D_{k}\in\mathcal{D}_{P}$ with $k\in P^{\prime}$ do $D_{k}^{\prime}=D_{k}\setminus\sum_{\ell=1}^{L}H_{\ell}; \mathcal{D}_{P^{\prime}}^{\prime}=\mathcal{D}_{P^{\prime}}^{\prime}+\{D_{k}^{\prime}\}$;
  - Perform shrinking of all $H_{1}, H_{2}, ..., H_{L}$. 
  - Let $D^{(S)}$, $D_{k}^{(S)}\in\mathcal{D}_{P^{\prime}}^{(S)}$, and $\mathcal{D}_{P^{\prime}}^{(S)}$ be obtained from $D^{\prime}$, $D_{k}^{\prime}\in\mathcal{D}_{P^{\prime}}^{\prime}$, and $\mathcal{D}_{P^{\prime}}^{\prime}$ by shrinking of all $H_{1}, H_{2}, ..., H_{L}$, respectively; 
  - $\operatorname{CutCake}(P^{\prime}, D^{(\bar{S})}, \mathcal{D}_{P^{\prime}}^{(S)})$; Perform inverse shrinking of all $H_{1}, H_{2}, ..., H_{L}$;

Note that, If $P^{\prime}\neq\emptyset$ after the deletion of $H_{1}, H_{2}, ..., H_{L}$ and $\operatorname{CutCake}(P^{\prime}, D^{(S)}, \mathcal{D}_{P^{\prime}}^{(S)})$ is recursively called, then the minimum density $\rho_{\mathrm{min}}^{\prime}$ in $\operatorname{CutCake}(P^{\prime}, D^{(S)}, D_{P^{\prime}}^{(S)})$ satisfies $\rho_{\mathrm{min}}^{\prime}>\rho_{\mathrm{min}}$ by Lemma 6. Next, we give a detailed description of $\operatorname{CutMaxInterval}\left(R, H, D_{R}\right)$ based on Lemma 7 and Procedure $\operatorname{CutMinInterval}(S, X, T_{S})$.

# Procedure $\operatorname{CutMaxInterval}(R, H, D_{R})$

- Let $X_{1}=\left[x_{1}^{\prime}, x_{1}^{\prime\prime}\right)$, $X_{2}=\left[x_{2}^{\prime}, x_{2}^{\prime\prime}\right)$, ..., $X_{K}=\left[x_{K}^{\prime}, x_{K}^{\prime\prime}\right]$ be all the minimal intervals of minimum density $\rho_{\mathrm{min}}$ in $H$. // $X_{1}, X_{2}, ..., X_{K}$ are mutually disjoint by Corollary 5.
- For $k=1$ to $K$ do 
  - cut cake $H$ at both endpoints $x_{k}^{\prime}, x_{k}^{\prime\prime}$ of $X_{k}$;
  - $S_{k}=\{i\in R \mid D_{i}\subseteq X_{k}, D_{i}\in\mathcal{D}_{R}\}$; $\mathcal{D}_{S_{k}}=\left(D_{i}\in\mathcal{D}_{R}: i\in S_{k}\right)$;
  - $\operatorname{CutMinInterval}(S_{k}, X_{k}, D_{S_{k}})$;
- $R^{\prime}=R; H^{\prime}=H$; for $k=1$ to $K$ do $R^{\prime}=R^{\prime}\setminus S_{k}; H^{\prime}=H^{\prime}\setminus X_{k};$;
- If $R^{\prime}\neq\emptyset$ then // $R^{\prime}=R\setminus\sum_{k=1}^{K}S_{k}$, $H^{\prime}=H\setminus\sum_{k=1}^{K}X_{k}$
  - $\mathcal{D}_{R^{\prime}}^{\prime}=\emptyset$;
  - For each $D_{i}\in\mathcal{D}_{R}$ with $i\in R^{\prime}$ do, $D_{i}^{\prime}=D_{i}\setminus\sum_{k=1}^{K}X_{k}$, $\mathcal{D}_{R^{\prime}}^{\prime}=\mathcal{D}_{R^{\prime}}^{\prime}+\{D_{i}^{\prime}\}$;
  - Perform shrinking of all $X_{1}, X_{2}, ..., X_{K}$;
  - Let $H^{(S)}$, $D_{i}^{(S)}\in\mathcal{D}_{R^{\prime}}^{(S)}$ and $\mathcal{D}_{R^{\prime}}^{(S)}$ be obtained from $H^{\prime}$, $D_{i}^{\prime}\in\mathcal{D}_{R^{\prime}}^{\prime}$ and $D_{R^{\prime}}^{\prime}$ by shrinking of all $X_{1}, X_{2}, ..., X_{K}$, respectively;
  - $\operatorname{CutMaxIntensity}(R^{\prime}, H^{(S)}, \mathcal{D}_{R^{\prime}}^{(S)})$; Perform inverse shrinking of all $X_{1}, X_{2}, ..., X_{K}$.

Note that, if $R^{\prime}\neq\emptyset$, $X_{1}, X_{2}, ..., X_{K}$ and $\operatorname{CutMaxInterval}(R^{\prime}, H^{(S)}, \mathcal{D}_{R^{\prime}}^{(S)})$ is recursively called, then the minimum density $\rho_{\mathrm{min}}^{\prime}$ in $\operatorname{CutMaxInterval}(R^{\prime}, H^{(S)}, \mathcal{D}_{R^{\prime}}^{(S)})$ satisfies $\rho_{\mathrm{min}}^{\prime}=\rho_{\mathrm{min}}$ by Lemma 7. As mentioned before, Procedure $\operatorname{CutMinInterval}\mathrm{l}(S, X, \mathcal{D}_{S})$ is the core method for solving the cake-cutting problem where cake $X$ is a minimal interval of minimum density in maximal interval $H$ of minimum density $\rho_{\mathrm{min}}$, players $S=R(X)=\{i\in R \mid D_{i}\in\mathcal{D}_{R}, D_{i}\subseteq X\}$ and solid valuation intervals $\mathcal{D}_{S}=\mathcal{D}_{R(X)}=(D_{i}\in\mathcal{D}_{R}: i\in S)$.
